      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:2:1",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ الثَّوْبُ النَّقِيُّ يَكْبِتُ الْعَدُوَّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ali bin Al Hakam, from Abdullah Bin Jundab, from Sufyan Bin Al Samt who said, ",
          "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The clean clothes suppress the enemy’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from Ali ibn al-Hakam from ‘Abd Allah ibn Jundab from Sufyan ibn al-Simt who has said the following: “I once heard abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, ‘Clean garments put down the enemy.’” "
        ]
      }
